Package fr.cnrs.iees.omhtk

Interface Sealable

public interface Sealable

This interface is for objects that can be modified for a certain time, and then be sealed so that no future change is permitted.

The typical use case is for objects that cannot be used until some late initialisation (i.e. after instantiation) is performed. It can be quite powerful when used in conjunction with the Initialisable interface.
